1. Install Git
2. Open command prompt
3. (git init) for new project without git.


4. (git add .) for adding all files.
5. (git commit -m "Commit Message") for committing any changes into your project.
6. (git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git) for initializing where to upload project into (Which Repository?)
7. (git push -u origin master) for pushing into GitHub or (git push).

For new laptop:
1. Install Git
2. Open command prompt
3. (git init) for new project without git.
4. (git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git) for initializing where to upload project into (Which Repository?)
5. (git pull)
